CLI flags
  --selftest           synthetic 6s split into 3×2s, phi monotone check
  --board <id>         board selector (default synthetic)
  --duration <int>     total session seconds (positive integer)
  --segment <int>      target segment seconds (positive integer; ≤ duration)
  --tag <str>          tag for basename
  --output <dir>       parent directory (default anima-eeg/recordings/sessions)
  --basename <str>     override auto basename
  --seed <int>         base seed (per-segment seed = base_seed + segment_index)
  --sample-rate <hz>   default 250.0
  --phi                enable phi proxy per segment (synthetic cos sweep)
  --list-boards        list supported boards

dual-stream coordination
  - Each segment optionally records phi_mean_proxy alongside EEG (--phi flag).
  - phi proxy in synthetic = cos sweep over [0, π] across segment indices
    (monotone-decreasing 1.0 → 0.5 → 0.0+ on n=3 segments).
  - Real phi sampling = anima_runtime hook (out of Phase 4 scope; raw#10 placeholder).

multi-segment splice
  - n_segments = ceil(total_duration / segment_target)
  - per-segment .npy + .json saved; top-level *_session.json indexes splices.
  - splice manifest does NOT concatenate .npy bytes — downstream consumers
    stitch via session.segments[].npy_path list (memory-friendly for hour-long sessions).
  - hard cap n_segments ≤ 9999 (helper-side ABORT).

